          en: "Elric, albino emperor of decadent Melniboné, is physically weak and depends on drugs and sorcery to survive. When he claims the black runesword Stormbringer, it grants him strength by drinking the souls of those it kills - friends and enemies alike. The sword is sentient, a demon trapped in blade form, and gradually dominates Elric's will, forcing him to kill those he loves to feed its hunger. Moorcock created the anti-Conan: a tortured, philosophical protagonist cursed by his power rather than empowered by it. The tragic cycle culminates in Stormbringer consuming everyone Elric loves, revealing the sword's true master. This influenced countless 'cursed weapon' narratives in fantasy.",
